352
00:31:44,816 --> 00:31:47,410
Some of this, some of that.

353
00:32:00,398 --> 00:32:02,127
Nothing's gonna bite you.

354
00:32:03,868 --> 00:32:05,927
You look like you're new in town.

355
00:32:06,137 --> 00:32:09,265
From what l can see,
you're pretty handy with a bottle.

356
00:32:09,474 --> 00:32:10,304
He had it coming.

357
00:32:11,876 --> 00:32:13,138
Pull up a chair.

358
00:32:23,822 --> 00:32:25,289
What do they call you?

359
00:32:25,657 --> 00:32:26,783
Red.

360
00:32:27,625 --> 00:32:28,853
And l ain't no punk.

361
00:32:29,127 --> 00:32:30,458
You better not be.

362
00:32:31,196 --> 00:32:33,892
Any cat toe you down here,
you stand up or make tracks.

363
00:32:34,098 --> 00:32:35,258
Man live by his rep.

364
00:32:35,533 --> 00:32:36,397
Better believe it.

365
00:32:37,902 --> 00:32:39,392
So what do you do?

366
00:32:39,604 --> 00:32:40,593
Working on the train.

367
00:32:42,340 --> 00:32:43,170
Like that job?

368
00:32:43,641 --> 00:32:47,270
-lKeeps me out of the Army.
-They want you, nothing'll keep you out.

369
00:32:47,479 --> 00:32:48,309
Not this boy.

370
00:32:50,248 --> 00:32:52,716
So l hear tell
you're a good man to know.

371
00:32:52,917 --> 00:32:54,942
-Where you hear that?
-Boston, where l'm from.

372
00:32:55,153 --> 00:32:56,677
lKiss my neck.

373
00:32:57,055 --> 00:32:58,579
l've never been in Beantown.

374
00:32:58,790 --> 00:33:01,623
Like the man said, a man's rep travels.

375
00:33:02,660 --> 00:33:03,991
How about that!

376
00:33:06,231 --> 00:33:07,357
You bullshitting me?

377
00:33:07,565 --> 00:33:10,591
My father told me
never bullshit a West lndian.

378
00:33:10,802 --> 00:33:12,030
Your daddy's West lndian?

379
00:33:12,237 --> 00:33:13,397
My mama.

380
00:33:14,072 --> 00:33:15,835
She's from Grenada.

381
00:33:16,140 --> 00:33:17,402
Grenada.

382
00:33:21,346 --> 00:33:22,210
l like this guy.

383
00:33:22,647 --> 00:33:24,547
l like your country.

384
00:33:25,350 --> 00:33:26,647
Grenada.

385
00:33:26,851 --> 00:33:29,411
Where'd you get them
goddamn vines you got on?

386
00:33:29,754 --> 00:33:31,312
And them shoes?

387
00:33:31,623 --> 00:33:32,453
Oh, my.

388
00:33:32,657 --> 00:33:34,090
We can do something about that.

389
00:33:34,292 --> 00:33:37,557
But he's putting a hurting
on my vision, man!

390
00:33:37,762 --> 00:33:38,922
Relax.

391
00:33:39,597 --> 00:33:40,621
How do l find you?

392
00:33:40,832 --> 00:33:42,026
You can't.

393
00:33:42,834 --> 00:33:44,199
l get ahold of you.

394
00:33:44,402 --> 00:33:46,563
All right, l'll write it down.

395
00:33:46,771 --> 00:33:48,602
Don't ever write anything down.

396
00:33:48,806 --> 00:33:50,535
File it up here.

397
00:33:50,875 --> 00:33:52,274
Like l do.

398
00:33:53,111 --> 00:33:56,512
lf the man don't have any paper,
he will never have any proof.

399
00:33:57,048 --> 00:33:58,106
Dig?

400
00:33:59,651 --> 00:34:02,245
Yeah, l dig. Right.

401
00:34:07,225 --> 00:34:08,351
Look me in the face.

402
00:34:08,560 --> 00:34:10,221
Did you just con me?

403
00:34:13,131 --> 00:34:14,223
Yes, sir.

404
00:34:14,632 --> 00:34:15,530
Why?

405
00:34:15,733 --> 00:34:17,257
Because l want in.

406
00:34:18,136 --> 00:34:20,798
lt don't take a lot to know
you're already there.

407
00:34:21,005 --> 00:34:22,666
At least he ain't lying.

408
00:34:22,874 --> 00:34:24,307
l have a run to make.

409
00:34:24,509 --> 00:34:26,841
Let me make that run
with you, Mr. Archie.

410
00:34:36,054 --> 00:34:37,043
l like your heart.

411
00:34:38,156 --> 00:34:39,817
l like your style.

412
00:34:40,758 --> 00:34:42,783
