No? Why not?

2476
03:00:08,051 --> 03:00:09,951
You had enough time, didn't you?

2477
03:00:10,153 --> 03:00:12,451
l apologize.
We'll have it next week.

2478
03:00:12,655 --> 03:00:14,953
We don't have next week.
We need it today.

2479
03:00:15,158 --> 03:00:17,524
The people want to hear
the charter today.

2480
03:00:17,727 --> 03:00:19,388
Next week, Minister.

2481
03:00:25,869 --> 03:00:27,234
ls the reverend here?

2482
03:00:27,570 --> 03:00:30,869
The reverend called and said
he wouldn't be able to attend.

2483
03:00:32,342 --> 03:00:35,834
So now we don't have
an opening speaker or a charter....

2484
03:00:36,646 --> 03:00:39,479
Why didn't you say this last night
when l talked to you?

2485
03:00:39,682 --> 03:00:42,549
-l called Sister Betty.
-You didn't have to call her!

2486
03:00:42,752 --> 03:00:44,720
You should've told me!
Why tell her?

2487
03:00:44,921 --> 03:00:47,185
-l assumed that--
-Don't assume anything!

2488
03:00:57,734 --> 03:00:58,894
Go on down front.

2489
03:00:59,202 --> 03:01:01,762
-Sister, you go on with the brother.
-Yes, sir.

2490
03:01:20,423 --> 03:01:21,617
What's wrong?

2491
03:01:26,129 --> 03:01:28,461
lt's a time for martyrs now.

2492
03:01:32,168 --> 03:01:34,033
The way l feel...

2493
03:01:35,471 --> 03:01:37,530
...l shouldn't go out there today.

2494
03:01:39,142 --> 03:01:41,633
Fine. Let's cancel it.

2495
03:01:44,647 --> 03:01:46,808
My wife out there?
My children?

2496
03:01:47,217 --> 03:01:49,208
Down front, as always.

2497
03:01:52,222 --> 03:01:54,884
Go out to the pay phone outside.

2498
03:01:56,392 --> 03:02:00,692
Call up the reverend,
see if he can make it down here.

2499
03:02:00,897 --> 03:02:02,694
l gotta be on post.

2500
03:02:02,899 --> 03:02:05,060
l'm supposed to be
guarding you.

2501
03:02:05,268 --> 03:02:10,205
-Besides, that's a duty for secretaries--
-Go out to the pay phone.

2502
03:02:10,740 --> 03:02:12,332
Call up the reverend.

2503
03:02:12,842 --> 03:02:14,673
See if he can make it down here.

2504
03:02:19,148 --> 03:02:20,342
Fine.

2505
03:03:15,705 --> 03:03:16,967
Thank you.

2506
03:03:21,778 --> 03:03:24,611
l apologize for
raising my voice earlier.

2507
03:03:24,814 --> 03:03:26,406
lt was very disrespectful.

2508
03:03:26,649 --> 03:03:29,140
Brother Minister, l understand.

2509
03:03:38,094 --> 03:03:39,391
Why styles are changing...

2510
03:03:39,729 --> 03:03:42,527
...minds are changing,
why everything is changing.

2511
03:03:43,199 --> 03:03:47,260
So you and l must consider that
we're living in very changing times.

2512
03:03:47,670 --> 03:03:51,128
And what might be true today
may not be true tomorrow.

2513
03:03:52,041 --> 03:03:54,703
And without any further ado,
l present to you...

2514
03:03:55,178 --> 03:03:57,874
...Brother Minister Malcolm.
And l pray...

2515
03:03:58,348 --> 03:04:02,045
...that you and l will listen.
Listen...

2516
03:04:02,685 --> 03:04:05,176
...hear and understand.

2517
03:04:05,388 --> 03:04:06,218
Thank you.

2518
03:04:13,229 --> 03:04:14,594
Daddy!

2519
03:04:28,878 --> 03:04:31,039
Get your hand out of my pocket!

2520
03:04:32,815 --> 03:04:33,907
Brother....

2521
03:04:34,117 --> 03:04:35,209
Please. Hold it.

2522
03:04:36,886 --> 03:04:38,877
Calm down.
Please, brothers!

2523
03:04:39,088 --> 03:04:40,020
Brothers....

2524
03:05:21,764 --> 03:05:23,857
Get an ambulance!

2525
03:05:24,066 --> 03:05:25,090
Get an ambulance!

2526
03:05:25,368 --> 03:05:26,494
They killed him!

2527
03:05:28,271 --> 03:05:30,262
They killed him!

2528
03:06:49,285 --> 03:06:50,718
Get out of the way!

2529
03:06:55,992 --> 03:06:56,822
Move!

2530
03:07:05,201 --> 03:07:06,566
Stand back!

2531
03:07:07,103 --> 03:07:08,092
Get back!

2532
03:07:10,039 --> 03:07:12,507
Give us a statement, sir!
Please!

2533
03:07:12,708 --> 03:07:16,144
The person you know
as Malcolm X is no more.

2534
03:07:16,479 --> 03:07:18,470
The assassination...

2535
03:07:18,714 --> 03:07:22,309
...of Malcolm X
was an unfortunate tragedy.

2536
03:07:22,718 --> 03:07:25,380
And it reveals
that there are still...

2537
03:07:25,721 --> 03:07:28,815
...numerous people
in our nation who have...

2538
03:07:29,058 --> 03:07:33,722
...degenerated to the point of
expressing dissent through murder...

2539
03:07:33,996 --> 03:07:36,294
...and we haven't learned
to disagree...

2540
03:07:36,499 --> 03:07:38,558
...without being
violently disagreeable.

2541
03:07:39,835 --> 03:07:40,893
Here...

2542
03:07:41,671 --> 03:07:44,333
...at this final hour...

2543
03:07:44,907 --> 03:07:47,171
...in this quiet place...

2544
03:07:47,877 --> 03:07:50,175
...Harlem has come to bid farewell...

2545
03:07:50,379 --> 03:07:52,779
...to one of its brightest hopes...

2546
03:07:53,816 --> 03:07:55,784
...extinguished now...

2547
03:07:56,252 --> 03:07:58,914
...and gone from us forever.

2548
03:07:59,822 --> 03:08:02,848
It is not in the memory
of man that this...

2549
03:08:03,059 --> 03:08:04,617
...beleaguered, unfortunate...

2550
03:08:04,827 --> 03:08:06,954
...but nonetheless proud community...

2551
03:08:07,363 --> 03:08:11,766
...has found a braver,
more gallant young champion...

2552
03:08:12,034 --> 03:08:15,492
...than this Afro-American
who lies before us...

2553
03:08:16,439 --> 03:08:18,430
...unconquered still.

2554
03:08:20,343 --> 03:08:22,709
I say the word again as
he would want me to:

2555
03:08:22,912 --> 03:08:24,277
Afro-American.

2556
03:08:24,513 --> 03:08:27,812
Afro-American Malcolm.

2557
03:08:28,017 --> 03:08:30,747
Malcolm had stopped being "Negro"...

2558
03:08:30,953 --> 03:08:32,284
...years ago.

2559
03:08:32,521 --> 03:08:37,458
It had become too small, too puny,
too weak a word for him.

2560
03:08:37,793 --> 03:08:39,988
Malcolm was bigger than that.

2561
03:08:40,296 --> 03:08:41,593
Malcolm had become...

2562
03:08:41,831 --> 03:08:44,061
...an Afro-American.

2563
03:08:44,333 --> 03:08:46,563
And he wanted so desperately...

2564
03:08:47,103 --> 03:08:49,697
...that we,
that all his people...

2565
03:08:49,905 --> 03:08:52,999
...would become Afro-Americans too.

2566
03:08:57,013 --> 03:09:00,471
There are those who
still consider it their duty...

2567
03:09:00,683 --> 03:09:04,380
...as friends of the Negro people,
to tell us...

2568
03:09:04,920 --> 03:09:06,649
...to revile him.

2569
03:09:06,856 --> 03:09:10,155
To flee, even from
the presence of his memory.

2570
03:09:10,359 --> 03:09:11,883
To save ourselves...

2571
03:09:12,094 --> 03:09:16,656
...by writing him out of
the history of our turbulent times.

2572
03:09:17,033 --> 03:09:19,092
And we will smile.

2573
03:09:19,402 --> 03:09:21,734
They will say that
he is of hate, a fanatic...

2574
03:09:21,937 --> 03:09:24,929
...a racist, who can only bring
evil to the cause...

2575
03:09:25,141 --> 03:09:26,574
...for which you struggle.

2576
03:09:26,776 --> 03:09:29,745
And we will answer and
say unto them:

2577
03:09:29,945 --> 03:09:31,913
"Did you ever talk...

2578
03:09:32,281 --> 03:09:33,942
...to Brother Malcolm?

2579
03:09:34,583 --> 03:09:36,414
Did you ever touch him...

2580
03:09:36,619 --> 03:09:38,746
...or have him smile at you?

2581
03:09:38,954 --> 03:09:41,286
Did you ever really listen to him?"

2582
03:09:43,526 --> 03:09:47,758
"Was he ever associated with violence
or any public disturbance?

2583
03:09:47,963 --> 03:09:50,864
For if you did, you would know him.

2584
03:09:51,067 --> 03:09:52,557
And if you knew him...

2585
03:09:52,802 --> 03:09:56,533
...you would know why
we must honor him. "

2586
03:09:56,739 --> 03:10:01,073
Malcolm was our manhood.
Our living, black manhood.

2587
03:10:01,310 --> 03:10:03,369
This was his meaning
to his people.

2588
03:10:03,646 --> 03:10:08,242
And in honoring him, we honor
the best in ourselves.

2589
03:10:09,618 --> 03:10:12,280
However much we may have
differed with him...

2590
03:10:12,488 --> 03:10:15,548
...or with each other about him
and his value as a man...

2591
03:10:15,758 --> 03:10:17,885
...let his going from us serve...

2592
03:10:18,094 --> 03:10:21,154
...only to bring us together now...

2593
03:10:22,164 --> 03:10:24,826
...consigning these mortal
remains to earth...

2594
03:10:25,334 --> 03:10:27,393
...the common mother of all...

2595
03:10:27,603 --> 03:10:30,936
...secure in the knowledge
that what we place in the ground...

2596
03:10:31,140 --> 03:10:32,471
...is no more now a man...

2597
03:10:32,742 --> 03:10:34,266
...but a seed...

2598
03:10:34,610 --> 03:10:37,579
...which after the winter of
our discontent...

2599
03:10:37,780 --> 03:10:40,647
...will come forth again
to meet us.

2600
03:10:40,850 --> 03:10:43,080
And we shall know him then...

2601
03:10:43,285 --> 03:10:46,152
...for what he was and is:

2602
03:10:46,355 --> 03:10:48,152
A prince.

2603
03:10:48,357 --> 03:10:51,952
Our own black shining prince...

2604
03:10:52,695 --> 03:10:55,858
...who didn't hesitate to die...

2605
03:10:56,198 --> 03:10:57,529
...because...

2606
03:10:58,200 --> 03:10:59,827
...he loved us so.

2607
03:11:00,569 --> 03:11:01,763
And so today...

2608
03:11:01,971 --> 03:11:05,134
...May 1 9, we celebrate
Malcolm X's birthday...

2609
03:11:05,374 --> 03:11:09,208
...because he was
a great, great Afro-American.

2610
03:11:09,478 --> 03:11:12,140
Malcolm X is you, all of you.

2611
03:11:12,548 --> 03:11:14,607
And you are Malcolm X.

2612
03:11:15,151 --> 03:11:16,175
l'm Malcolm X!

2613
03:11:16,385 --> 03:11:17,443
l'm Malcolm X!

2614
03:11:17,720 --> 03:11:18,618
l'm Malcolm X!

2615
03:11:28,063 --> 03:11:30,554
As Brother Malcolm said:

2616
03:11:33,402 --> 03:11:35,336
"We declare...

2617
03:11:36,672 --> 03:11:38,333
...our right...

2618
03:11:40,476 --> 03:11:42,171
...on this earth...

2619
03:11:43,546 --> 03:11:45,138
...to be a man...

2620
03:11:47,383 --> 03:11:49,544
...to be a human being...

2621
03:11:51,821 --> 03:11:54,221
...to be given the rights...

2622
03:11:54,990 --> 03:11:56,719
...of a human being...

2623
03:11:58,561 --> 03:12:00,392
...to be respected...

2624
03:12:01,564 --> 03:12:03,828
...as a human being...

2625
03:12:04,733 --> 03:12:06,997
...in this society...

2626
03:12:08,237 --> 03:12:10,068
...on this earth...

2627
03:12:11,574 --> 03:12:13,405
...in this day...

2628
03:12:14,009 --> 03:12:16,637
...which we intend to bring...

2629
03:12:16,846 --> 03:12:18,177
...into existence--"

2630
03:12:18,380 --> 03:12:21,213
--by any means necessary!
